description:
Recently sold: $354,500. The home was designed in 1997 by Wayne Branum, renowned Stillwater architect and potter. With nearly 2,600 sq. ft., it sits on 7.8 acres, a field away from Wild River State Park. Grand oaks and maples surround the home, and magnificent pines protect it from the north winds.  The views of the St. Croix River Valley are spectacular. A world away, but less than one hour from downtown Minneapolis or St. Paul. This home has 3 bedrooms, and a whirlpool bath.  There are two bedrooms downstairs with an additional spacious bedroom, office, family room, and loft upstairs. The gourmet kitchen and open design make this house perfect for entertaining.  In-floor heating and a polished block space for a woodstove make this house cozy in the winter. The house has central air, but it's rarely used because of the home's incredible windows throughout. 

 This year we replaced the roof, painted the house and installed new carpeting.  The 1,050 garage was built within the last five years and is large enough for two cars, and a shop or studio.  The acreage is perfect for horses and organic gardening with mature apple trees and blackberries. Sugar maples abound on the property, and making your own maple syrup is a local tradition.  If you visit, you'll want to stay.  See you Sunday!

Neighborhood Description



Tree lined streets.  Friendly, helpful neighbors.  Next to Minnesota Interstate Park.

description: Recently sold: $295,000. Classic architecturally designed modern farmhouse. Home is rambler style that fits in perfectly with its surroundings. One-of-a-kind design & beautifully decorated - shows perfectly. Relax in your corn crib fire pit area on a quiet country evening, Close to Wild Mountain skiing, Wild River State Park & area winery. Home is gorgeous on inside with hardwood laminate & tile floors, panel doors, vaults and wooden staircase. Open design in living-dining-kitchen area. Large granite island & lots of windows that bring in the natural light. Main level also has an office area just off foyer/mud room area.  Bath on main is designed as walk-thru for easy use from master, kitchen, & office. Great for traffic flow. Walkout lower level has 3 separate BR's surrounding a family area with cozy stove heater. Outside there is detached 4-car garage, she shed/chicken coop, paver patios & walkways. 50 yr metal roof with cupola, architectural columns, large yard & lots of wildlife. Welcome to the country!
